{
  "doc_id": "999",
  "text": "The obligate biotrophic downy mildews constitute the most species-rich group within the oomycetes [CITATION_1] , and are derived from Phytophthora-like ancestors [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] . So far, their monophyly could not be ascertained, even though Runge et al. [CITATION_6] obtained high support for a grouping of the two major lineages of the downy mildews included in their study. Based on phylogenomic investigations with limited taxon sampling, downy mildews were inferred to be the sister-group to Phytophthora [CITATION_7] [CITATION_8] , contradicting earlier reports in which downy mildews were proposed to be nested within Phytophthora [CITATION_9] [CITATION_10] [CITATION_11] .",
